                    <p rend="flushleft">I. <hi rend="italic">Peace Treaty With Italy</hi></p>
                    <p>The Deputies proceeded, on the instructions of the Ministers, to discuss the
                        following agenda: <list>
                            <label>(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                            <item>Text of Article 16 (Free Territory of Trieste)</item>
                            <label>(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                            <item>List of questions still outstanding in the draft treaty.</item>
                        </list></p>
                    <list>
                        <label>(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                        <item><hi rend="italic">Article 16</hi>.</item>
                        <label/>
                        <item>An exchange of views took place on the text of this Article to be
                            submitted for the consideration of the Ministers. Alternative texts
                            submitted by the U.S.S.R. Delegation (Annex 1) and by the French United
                            States, and United Kingdom Delegations (Annex 2) are annexed for
                            information to the present Record.<note n="92" xml:id="d351fn92">Annexes
                                1 and 2 not printed.</note></item>
                        <label>(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                        <item><hi rend="italic">List of Outstanding Questions</hi>.</item>
                        <label/>
                        <item>The annex list of Articles or questions still outstanding on the
                            Italian Treaty was <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> (Annex 3).</item>
                    </list>
                    <p rend="flushleft">II. <hi rend="italic">Next Meeting</hi></p>
                    <p>Monday, November 25, 1946, at 11 a.m.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <dateline rendition="#left">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-11-26">November 26,
                                1946</date>.</dateline>
                    </closer>
                    <pb facs="1279" n="1255" xml:id="pg_1255"/>
                    <frus:attachment>
                        <head>Annex 3</head>
                        <p rend="center"><hi rend="smallcaps">List of Articles of the Draft Peace
                                Treaty With Italy Which Are Still Unagreed</hi></p>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Art. 3—Frontier between Italy and Yugoslavia.</p>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Art. 4—Frontier between Italy and the Free Territory of
                            Trieste.</p>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Art. 10 bis—Austro-Italian Agreement of September 5,
                            1946.</p>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Art. 16, para. 2—Frontier between Yugoslavia and the
                            Free Territory of Trieste.</p>
                        <list>
                            <item>Paras. 1, 3, 4, 5 of the US Proposal in the text of the Conference
                                Recommendation.</item>
                            <item>Para. 9—Powers of the Governor in cases not admitting of
                                delay.</item>
                            <item>Para. 10<hi rend="italic">b</hi>—Citizenship.</item>
                            <item>Para. 11—Free Port and Economic Questions: <list>
                                    <item>Provisional Government.</item>
                                    <item>Withdrawal of troops from the Free Territory.</item>
                                    <item>Provisional Regime; Statute of the Free Territory of
                                        Trieste. (Section 1 of the French Proposal—Resolution of the
                                        Conference).</item>
                                    <item>Clauses on the Free Port of Trieste.</item>
                                </list></item>
                        </list>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Art. 25A—Recognition of Albania as an Allied and
                            Associated Power.</p>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Art. 64, Part B, para. 1—Reparation for Albania,
                            Ethiopia, Greece and Yugoslavia.</p>
                        <list>
                            <item>Paras. 2(<hi rend="italic">c</hi>), 6, 7 (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>), (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>), (<hi rend="italic">c</hi>)
                                (Doc. <gloss target="#t_CFM46NY1">CFM(46) (NY)</gloss>17).<note n="93" xml:id="d351fn93">Report of the Committee of Economic
                                    Experts to the Deputies on the Peace Treaties with Italy and
                                    Rumania, November 16, 1946, circulated to the Council as
                                    document <gloss target="#t_CFM46NY1">CFM(46) (NY)</gloss>17,
                                    November 18, 1946, <ref target="#pg_1196">p.
                                1196</ref>.</note></item>
                            <item>Part D—Reparation for other Powers (Doc. <gloss target="#t_CFM46NY1">CFM(46) (NY)</gloss>20).<note n="94" xml:id="d351fn94">Second Report of the Committee of Economic
                                    Experts, <gloss target="#t_CFM46NY1">CFM(46) (NY)</gloss>20,
                                    November 21, 1946, <ref target="#pg_1227">p.
                                1227</ref>.</note></item>
                            <item>Part E—Compensation to Italian nationals for property removed for
                                Reparation purposes (Doc. <gloss target="#t_CFM46NY1">CFM(46)
                                    (NY)</gloss>17).</item>
                        </list>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Art. 67—Claims on Germany (Doc. <gloss target="#t_CFM46NY1">CFM(46) (NY)</gloss>20, para. 5).</p>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Art. 67, para. 4 (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>), (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>), (<hi rend="italic">c</hi>), (<hi rend="italic">d</hi>)—Compensation for Damage to United Nations
                            property in Italy.</p>
                        <list>
                            <item>Addition to para. 8(<hi rend="italic">c</hi>)—Definition of Ships
                                (Doc. <gloss target="#t_CFM1">CFM</gloss> (NY)17, para. 3).</item>
                        </list>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Art. 69—Italian Property in the territory of Allied and
                            Associated Powers.</p>
                        <list>
                            <item>Para. 5 (<hi rend="italic">e</hi>), (<hi rend="italic">f</hi>) of
                                the Draft Treaty—Property in Ceded Territories.</item>
                        </list>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Art. 71—General Economic Relations</p>
                        <list>
                            <item>Para. 1—Time-limit for Art. 71.</item>
                            <item>1(<hi rend="italic">c</hi>) Private Enterprises; Civil
                                Aviation.</item>
                        </list>
                        <pb facs="1280" n="1256" xml:id="pg_1256"/>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Art. 72—Settlement of Disputes—in connection with
                            Articles 65, 68 and Annexes 6, 7, and 8.</p>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Art. 74 bis—Non-participation of Italy in the
                            International Financial Commission in Greece.</p>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Art. 76—Settlement of Disputes concerning the
                            interpretation and execution of the Treaty.</p>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Art. 77 bis—Non-participation in the benefits of the
                            Treaty by countries which have not ratified it.</p>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Annex III—Economic and Financial Provisions relating to
                            Ceded Territories (referred to the Economic Experts).</p>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Annex VI—Part B. Insurance. (<gloss target="#t_CFM46NY1">CFM(46) (NY)</gloss>20, para. 6).</p>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Annex VII—Part I—Contracts. (<gloss target="#t_CFM46NY1">CFM(46) (NY)</gloss>20, para. 2).</p>
                        <list>
                            <item>Part II—Periods of Prescription (<gloss target="#t_CFM46NY1">CFM(46) (NY)</gloss>20, para, 3).</item>
                            <item>Part IV—Miscellaneous (<gloss target="#t_CFM46NY1">CFM(46)
                                    (NY)</gloss>20, para. 4).</item>
                            <item>Part V—Special Provision relating to the USA.</item>
                        </list>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Annex IX—Free Territory of Trieste (Water and
                            Electricity Supplies).</p>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Annex XIII—Property and Debts Provisions relating to the
                            Free Territory of Trieste.</p>
